            Yes. Because the scanner only reads <strong>publicly visible frontend code</strong>, you can scan any public Shopify store — including competitor stores — without any authentication. This makes it a powerful competitive intelligence tool.
            <br /><br />
            Use it to understand what apps your competitors are paying for, how their stack compares to yours, and whether they're using tools you haven't considered. Simply switch to <strong>Competitor Store</strong> mode and enter their domain.
            <br /><br />
            Common use cases for competitor scanning include benchmarking your operational costs, identifying emerging platforms gaining traction in your niche, and validating whether premium tools are standard in your industry or an avoidable overhead.
          </div>
        </div>
