      <div class="accordion-item" id="acc-4">
        <button class="accordion-trigger" id="acc-btn-4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acc-body-4">
          <h2>The Hidden Costs of a Bloated Shopify App Stack</h2>
          <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body" id="acc-body-4" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn-4">
          <div class="accordion-content">
            Monthly subscription fees are only part of the cost of running multiple Shopify apps. Each installed application loads <strong>additional scripts and resources</strong> on your storefront, increasing page load time and reducing Core Web Vitals scores — directly impacting SEO and conversion rates.
            <br /><br />
            Large app stacks also create <strong>operational complexity</strong>: overlapping functionality, data synchronisation failures between services, and integration fragility. For high-growth brands, these hidden costs often exceed the original subscription fees.
            <br /><br />
            Research consistently shows that a <strong>100ms improvement in page load time</strong> correlates with a 1% increase in revenue. Apps that load 300–500ms of additional scripts can silently cost more in lost conversions than their monthly subscription.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accordion-item" id="acc-5">
