        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body" id="acc-body-5" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn-5">
          <div class="accordion-content">
            Your <strong>automation efficiency score</strong> ranges from 0 to 100. Lower scores indicate higher SaaS dependency and greater monthly software spending relative to what's achievable with free alternatives. Higher scores indicate a leaner, more optimised stack.
            <br /><br />
            The score is not a measure of store revenue or success — it reflects the <strong>efficiency of your operational infrastructure</strong> and highlights opportunities to simplify. Key benchmarks:
            <ul>
              <li><strong>80–100:</strong> Excellent — minimal unnecessary overhead, well-optimised stack</li>
              <li><strong>60–79:</strong> Good — some apps replaceable, moderate savings available</li>
              <li><strong>40–59:</strong> Moderate — significant savings opportunity, multiple apps to review</li>
              <li><strong>0–39:</strong> High overhead — stack heavily dependent on paid apps; major savings available</li>
            </ul>
